investigation.title: Predicting how varying moisture conditions impact the microbiome of dust collected from the International Space Station (ISS)
investigation.description: On Earth, people spend 90% of their time indoors where dust and moisture can facilitate rapid microbial growth, especially fungi. The International Space Station is a specialized closed environment that contains own unique indoor microbiome.

publications.title: Fungal diversity differences in the indoor dust microbiome from built environments on earth and in space.
